channel.title: [PI] Adding dialogues and I got these errors, can someone help? [REP++]
channel.description:
So, I'm creating a tutorial for my source, it consists of dialogues at the moment but will have camera rotations as well, but I've got these 11 errors that have nothing to do with the case id's I've edited.
It started off at 100 errors, and I've gotten it down to 10, so if anyone can help with the final 10 I'd be grateful, here they are:
[code=java] src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:801: orphaned case case 9158: ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1653: illegal start of typ e if (c.isAutoButton(actionButtonId)) ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1653: <identifier> expecte d if (c.isAutoButton(actionButtonId)) ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1653: ';' expected if (c.isAutoButton(actionButtonId)) ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1653: illegal start of typ e if (c.isAutoButton(actionButtonId)) ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1653: <identifier> expecte d if (c.isAutoButton(actionButtonId)) ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1653: ';' expected if (c.isAutoButton(actionButtonId)) ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1654: illegal start of typ e c.assignAutocast(actionButtonId); ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1654: <identifier> expecte d c.assignAutocast(actionButtonId); ^ src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1657: class, interface, or enum expected } ^ 10 errors Press any key to continue . . . [/code]
5++ Rep to whoever fixes it.
